  "ciliary_role": "Also known as Nesprin1. Integral components of ciliary rootlets of multiciliated cells. Interacts with rootletin (28625779). Essential for the relocalisation of centrosome proteins and components of microtubule motor complexes to the nuclear envelope, and interacts with PCM-1 (27802164). Mutations are associated with cerebellar and non-cerebellar pathologies of unknown molecular pathogenesis (29630990). Mediates centrosome migration and determi tionof centrosome/basal body positioning during early cell polarization, an essential step for ciliogenesis (19596800).",
